			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Also, if you want to make group macros more interesting and a little more literally correct (this coming from an Ogre..  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> ), in addition to the %t variable used for your current target, there are others. Keep in mind that, just like %T, all of these commands refer to your CURRENT target, in different manners. The only exception is %M.
<br />
%T = current target. Example: 
<br />
         your current target: Orc centurion
<br />
         you type: /g %t incoming!
<br />
         your chat screen reads: You tell your group, "Orc centurion incoming!"
<br />

<br />
%O = objective pronoun i.e. he,she,it Example: 
<br />
         your current target: Priest of Discord
<br />
         you type: %o is twinked with summoned mage gear
<br />
         your chat screen reads: You say, "he is twinked with summoned mage gear."
<br />

<br />
%S = subjective pronoun i.e. her,him,it Example: 
<br />
         your current target: pained unicorn
<br />
         you type: /gu found %t . Run from %s !!!
<br />
         your chat screen reads: You tell your guild, "found pained unicorn . Run from it !!!"
<br />

<br />
%P = posessive pronoun i.e. her,his,its Example: 
<br />
         your current target: Ella Foodcrafter
<br />
         you type: /g i stole %p picanick basket!
<br />
         your chat screen reads: You tell your group, "i stole her picanick basket!"
<br />

<br />
%M = this refers to your pet's name, no matter what you have targeted. Example: 
<br />
         your current target: Scalebone skeleton
<br />
         you type: %m , attack %t .Sic %s ,now!
<br />
         your chat screen reads: You say, "Jobober , attack Scalebone skeleton .Sic it ,now!
<br />

<br />
well...those are the most basic and important ones, i'm sure there's more, though i'm not sure what they are. I think there's one that refers to yourself... /shrug ....anyway...play around with it in your macros.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Deling Albatross*51 Elementalist
<br />
Lonestarr Wanderlust*36 Ranger
<br />
Angmahr*16 Necromancer
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Have you hugged an Iksar today?
<br />
No. Have you shaved a Vah Shir today?</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
