			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You mentioned that with your pet sometimes when attacking multiple mobs, switches targets mid fight.  You said that you just "notice" which mob is getting "pet nuked" and switch.  I just wanted to give you the tactic I use for that.
<br />

<br />
Whenever I notice my pet switch targets I have one of my hotkeys set to "Pet back off".  I press that twice and then "Pet attack" (another hotkey) on the target I have been continually fighting and he readjusts who he attacks, so I don't have to.  He really doesn't lose many attacks, and you really never have to stop fighting a single target.  (Unless of course you want to just FoL the other sucker)
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, just another tactic someone may want to consider.  I find this personally easier than constantly re/assisting my pet to make sure we are both fighting the same mob.
<br />

<br />
Great writeup by the way!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
